    • Method Detail

      • addByteRows

        java.lang.Boolean addByteRows​(byte[] b)
                       throws XmlRpcException
        Add multiple measurements as a byte array, existing records with same sampling time and series id are skipped
        Parameters:
        b - byte array composed of
        1. series id as four bytes integer, high byte first
        2. sampling time in number of milliseconds since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 GM as eight bytes long, high byte first.
        3. measurement value as 4-byte float quantity according to the IEEE 754 floating-point "single format" bit layout
        Returns:
        Boolean
        Throws:
        XmlRpcException
        Since:
        1.7
        See Also:
        floatToRawIntBits

      • getRows

        java.util.Vector getRows​(java.lang.Integer id,
                         java.util.Vector timeFilter,
                         java.util.Vector statusFilter)
                  throws XmlRpcException
        Get rows of a series by status and time filter definition
        Parameters:
        id -
        timeFilter - vector of values
        1. start as Date
        2. end as Date
        statusFilter - vector of status values as int
        Returns:
        vector composed of two elements
        1. vector of column metadata
        2. vector of row values, a row is composed as a 9 byte array:

          [0,3] sampling time in number of milliseconds since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 GM /1000 as int

          [4,8] value as float

          [9] status as short

        element 1 is a byte array composed of rows, byte array format: Sampling Time/1000 as Integer, measurement value as Float, status quality flag as Byte
        Throws:
        XmlRpcException
        See Also:
        ILookUpTableHandler.getStatus()
